| NFL Reports, Player Updates                                              |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------------+

Latest NFL Player News

Kordell Stewart, QB PIT - Team Dick Updated 10/12/01
Don't expect Stewart to help your Fantasy team this week. The Steelers had
success running the ball last week, using a two-pronged attack, and will
stick to that strategy. Besides, Stewart won't be too effective when he
finally does throw the ball. He hasn't thrown a touchdown pass in three
games this season. 

Troy Edwards, WR PIT - Free Agent Updated 10/12/01
Edwards will catch a few passes this week but he won't be productive enough
to help a Fantasy team. The Steelers will run the ball for most of the
game. 

Amos Zereoue, RB PIT - Texas Terminators Updated 10/12/01
Amos might become famous soon enough if he continues to run like he did
last week. Look for him to continue to run well this week against the
Chiefs and score a touchdown. 

Plaxico Burress, WR PIT - DRock's Beaatchs Updated 10/12/01
Burress' struggles will continue again this week, but it won't be solely
because of his effort. The Steelers will implement a strict running game.
They were extremely successful running the ball last week. Also, Burress
won't get open enough to be productive.

Warrick Dunn, RB TB - President Taft Updated 10/12/01
Dunn tested his sprained right foot in practice Friday and could return to
Tampa Bay's lineup against the Tennessee Titans. His status for this week
was upgraded from questionable to probable Friday, though a decision on
whether he will play won't be made until Sunday. If he is cleared to play,
Dunn expects to assume his normal workload. But he is a risky Fantasy start
because of his uncertain condition. Dunn won't put up good numbers if he is
less than 100 percent. 

Brian Griese, QB DEN - Really Rottens Updated 10/12/01
Griese is now listed as questionable for Week Five with a sore shoulder,
but he is expected to play against the Seahawks. He was able to practice
without any apparent problems on Friday.

Bobby Engram, WR SEA - Free Agent Updated 10/12/01
Engram has developed a good on-field relationship with Trent Dilfer. He
might post solid numbers for the second consecutive week.

Darrell Jackson, WR SEA - Grid Iron Goons Updated 10/12/01
Jackson has started to fade away as a Fantasy receiver. If Bobby Engram
continues to play well. Jackson will get less looks from the Seattle QBs.

Trent Dilfer, QB SEA - Grid Iron Goons Updated 10/12/01
Dilfer will start for the second consecutive week. Expect him to throw at
least one TD pass against Denver, but the Seahawks will lean heavily on the
run against the Broncos.

Shaun Alexander, RB SEA - Houston Big Ballers Updated 10/12/01
Alexander is definitely a good start this week. He should score at least
one TD against the questionable Denver defense.

Koren Robinson, WR SEA - Orange Roughy Updated 10/12/01
Robinson should get more opportunities to catch the ball when Trent Dilfer
is playing. But he has yet to prove he can put up quality Fantasy numbers.

Charlie Garner, RB OAK - Luccis Losers Updated 10/12/01
Garner might be a major offensive factor this week. The Colts are soft
against the run, and Tyrone Wheatley is questionable with a wrist injury.
Garner might be asked to carry the ball often against the weak Indianapolis
run defense.

Tyrone Wheatley, RB OAK - Uran Man Updated 10/12/01
Wheatley is listed as questionable for Sunday's game against with a wrist
injury. Charlie Garner will get the majority of the carries if Wheatley is
not ready to play against the Colts.

Jerry Rice, WR OAK - Team Chick Updated 10/12/01
Rice should have another good outing. He should draw inexperienced
Indianapolis CB David Macklin in coverage, which means Rice will definitely
be a TD threat again this week.

Rich Gannon, QB OAK - Team Chick Updated 10/12/01
Gannon should have a fine game against the Colts. Indianapolis will have a
lot of trouble handling wideouts Tim Brown and Jerry Rice.

Freddie Jones, TE SD - DRock's Beaatchs Updated 10/12/01
Jones has been a disappointment so far this year. Don't count on good
numbers from him this week, because the Chargers will feature the run
against New England.

Jeff Graham, WR SD - Really Rottens Updated 10/12/01
Graham might be a good start against New England. He should be able to get
open often against CB Otis Smith.

Curtis Conway, WR SD - Blue Balls Updated 10/12/01
Conway is a risky start this week. The Chargers will feature their ground
game against New England, and CB Ty Law won't let Conway stray too far from
his view.

Doug Flutie, QB SD - President Taft Updated 10/12/01
The Patriots seem like a soft opponent, but don't expect Flutie to post
super totals. The Chargers will depend on the run to spur them to victory.

Desmond Clark, TE DEN - Really Rottens Updated 10/12/01
Consider Clark as a starter this week. The Seahawks are soft over the
middle and in the red zone, where Clark can be effective.

Dwayne Carswell, TE DEN - Free Agent Updated 10/12/01
Carswell is a good start this week. Seattle's defense has always been
vulnerable to tight ends over the middle.

Rod Smith, WR DEN - Blue Balls Updated 10/12/01
Smith's yardage numbers might be a bit disappointing this week if Seattle
CB Shawn Springs (hamstring, probable) is close to top form. But he should
still catch at least one TD pass as the Seahawks hurt their secondary with
the lack of a solid pass rush.

Mike Anderson, RB DEN - Really Rottens Updated 10/12/01
Expect excellent numbers from Anderson this week. He always plays well
against Seattle, and the Seahawks still lack the talent to stop him from
gaining big chunks of yardage as the game wears on.

Brian Griese, QB DEN - Really Rottens Updated 10/12/01
Griese should be good for at least two TD passes against the Seahawks. He
should have a lot of time to throw against the weak Seattle pass rush.

Marvin Minnis, WR KC - Houston Big Ballers Updated 10/12/01
Minnis might be asked to be Kansas City's No. 1 receiver this week, because
Derrick Alexander is expected to sit out with a back injury. That is a
major task for a rookie receiver. Facing the physical Pittsburgh defense
will limit Minnis' output, and he is a risky start.

Tony Gonzalez, TE KC - Grid Iron Goons Updated 10/12/01
Gonzalez might a major factor in Kansas City's passing game this week.
Trent Green will struggle to find open wideouts, and will look to Gonzalez
to help him move the ball on important downs.

Jermaine Wiggins, TE NE - Free Agent Updated 10/12/01
Wiggins has done very little to improve his Fantasy value this season. He's
not worth a roster spot at this point, so release him if you took a chance
on him early in the season. 

Priest Holmes, RB KC - Houston Big Ballers Updated 10/12/01
Don't expect great numbers from Holmes this week. Pittsburgh has been tough
against the run, and has the speed at LB to contain him on the outside.

Derrick Alexander, WR KC - C-Dawg's Boyz Updated 10/12/01
Alexander practiced on Thursday, but he is still being bothered by back
problems. If he is able to play against Pittsburgh, he will be very
limited.

David Patten, WR NE - Grid Iron Goons Updated 10/12/01
Patten now moves in the starting lineup as New England's No. 2 wideout due
to the release of Bert Emanuel. It will be a short-lived stint, however,
because Terry Glenn is expected to return to the team soon. As a result,
Patten isn't worth much more than a reserve spot Fantasy-wise. 

Trent Green, QB KC - Blue Balls Updated 10/12/01
Green might have another bad week. Pittsburgh's defense will pressure him
often, and the Chiefs will be less effective in the air without the injured
Derrick Alexander.

Tom Brady, QB NE - Free Agent Updated 10/12/01
Brady's numbers have been anything but impressive in Drew Bledsoe's
absence. He isn't really worthy of Fantasy consideration, so don't pick him
up for your roster. 

Ken Dilger, TE IND - Free Agent Updated 10/12/01
Dilger might be a minor factor in the passing game against Oakland. He
should get more looks this week, because the Colts have been hit hard by
injuries at wide receiver.

Phil Dawson, K CLE - Free Agent Updated 10/12/01
Look for Dawson to connect on a few field goals this week. The Browns will
have trouble capitalizing inside the red zone but Dawson will help them
score with accurate kicking. 

Jon Kitna, QB CIN - Blue Balls Updated 10/12/01
Look for Kitna to complete a fair amount of passes this week and score at
least one touchdown. The Browns defense will be tough, but Kitna will find
a way to get at least one score. 

Terry Glenn, WR NE - Grid Iron Goons Updated 10/12/01
Head Coach Bill Belichick has given Glenn a 50-50 chance of playing on
Sunday against San Diego. However, the veteran wideout is not worth
starting from a Fantasy perspective this week. 

Marcus Pollard, TE IND - Free Agent Updated 10/12/01
Pollard should find himself in a position to score this week. Indianapolis
should move the ball consistently in the air against Oakland.

J.R. Redmond, RB NE - Team Dick Updated 10/12/01
Redmond is questionable for Sunday's game against San Diego due to an ankle
injury. He probably will miss this game due to the injury, which makes him
virtually worthless Fantasy-wise. 

Marvin Harrison, WR IND - C-Dawg's Boyz Updated 10/12/01
Harrison should be able to get past the 100-yard receiving mark against the
Raiders. Oakland's secondary sometimes gives up big plays to the league's
better speed receivers.

Corey Dillon, RB CIN - Texas Terminators Updated 10/12/01
Look for Dillon to have mixed success this week. The Browns defense will
make it difficult to run but his effort as a receiver will be enough to
give him a productive week. 

Edgerrin James, RB IND - President Taft Updated 10/12/01
James' rushing yardage numbers might not be stellar against Oakland. But
the Colts will put him in position to score more than once.

Peyton Manning, QB IND - Orange Roughy Updated 10/12/01
Manning should throw at least two TD passes against Oakland. The Raiders'
secondary runs hot and cold, and sometimes has trouble with marquee
quarterbacks.

Peter Warrick, WR CIN - Dont Mess Updated 10/12/01
Warrick is suffering from a leg injury but is expected to play this week.
He won't be too productive. Warrick only has 18 catches in four games and
has scored just once. 

Darnay Scott, WR CIN - Orange Roughy Updated 10/12/01
Scott won't be too productive this week. He only averages four catches a
game and hasn't scored a touchdown. Rookie Chad Johnson might cut into his
playing time. 

Quincy Carter, QB DAL - Free Agent Updated 10/12/01
Carter needs surgery to repair his torn hamstring and will be lost for up
to eight weeks. Anthony Wright will start in Carter's place, but neither QB
has much Fantasy value at this point. 

Mike Vanderjagt, K IND - C-Dawg's Boyz Updated 10/12/01
Vanderjagt (toe) kicked in practice on Thursday. He is expected to play
against the Raiders.

Elvis Grbac, QB BAL - Houston Big Ballers Updated 10/12/01
As has been the popular theme in Baltimore, Grbac will throw the ball a lot
this week. He won't be too accurate but will connect for at least one
touchdown pass. 

Brandon Stokley, WR BAL - Free Agent Updated 10/12/01
Stokley won't be productive this week. He has had problems getting open.
That is part of the reason why he lost his starting job. 

Shannon Sharpe, TE BAL - Orange Roughy Updated 10/12/01
Sharpe will be very effective in a hard-fought game against the Packers
this week. He will catch a lot of passes and most likely score on a short
pass. 

Curtis Martin, RB NYJ - Grid Iron Goons Updated 10/12/01
Martin should register at least one TD against the Dolphins. The Jets are
not intimidated by Miami's defense, and will put their star RB in position
to score inside the red zone.

Travis Taylor, WR BAL - DRock's Beaatchs Updated 10/12/01
Taylor will have another solid game this week. Expect him to catch several
passes and use his height to snag a touchdown pass or two. 

Vinny Testaverde, QB NYJ - Uran Man Updated 10/12/01
Testaverde is a risky start this week. While he might throw more than one
TD pass, he also might turn the ball over more than once against Miami.

Terry Allen, RB BAL - Texas Terminators Updated 10/12/01
Don't expect Allen to get a lot of yards this week. However, he might score
a touchdown. The Ravens have been getting him a lot of carries once they
get close to the goal line. 

Qadry Ismail, WR BAL - Blue Balls Updated 10/12/01
Ismail will catch several passes this week but don't expect him to score.
The Ravens will spread the ball around a lot in their passing attack and
will look to Shannon Sharpe and Travis Taylor once they get inside the red
zone. 

James McKnight, WR MIA - Luccis Losers Updated 10/12/01
McKnight will definitely be a TD threat this week. He should be able to get
loose for some long gains.

Oronde Gadsden, WR MIA - Team Dick Updated 10/12/01
Gadsden should find himself in position to catch a TD pass against the
Jets. Miami will score often against the New York defense.

Frank Wycheck, TE TEN - DRock's Beaatchs Updated 10/12/01
Look for Wycheck to catch a lot of passes this week. He hasn't had a lot of
looks because he has been used mostly as a fullback, blocking for Eddie
George. But George is suffering from an ankle injury and isn't expected to
get a lot of carries. The Titans will throw to Wycheck to compensate. 

Lamar Smith, RB MIA - Texas Terminators Updated 10/12/01
Smith should have a super day against the Jets. New York hasn't stopped
anyone on the ground, and Smith has run over everyone he has faced so far.

Steve McNair, QB TEN - Luccis Losers Updated 10/12/01
The Titans normally implement a strict running game in their offense. But
with RB Eddie George suffering from an ankle injury they will throw the
ball a lot on Sunday. McNair will be able to move the chains using short
passes but he won't beat anyone deep. He has had troubles throwing the deep
ball and will face a lot of pressure from the Tampa pass rush. He will
connect on short passes, but is more apt to run for a touchdown. 

Michael Bennett, RB MIN - Houston Big Ballers Updated 10/12/01
Bennett was held in check once again last Sunday, posting only 36 yards of
total offense against New Orleans. He may be worth starting in deeper
leagues against Detroit, however, but we'd avoid him if at all possible. 

Jay Fiedler, QB MIA - C-Dawg's Boyz Updated 10/12/01
Fiedler should have a good week against the Jets. New York's pass defense
will surrender at least two TDs if it cannot effectively pressure the Miami
QB.

Kevin Dyson, WR TEN - Free Agent Updated 10/12/01
Dyson will get a lot of passes thrown his way this week. Although fellow
wideout Derrick Mason is suffering from injuries starting RB Eddie George
is also injured. Look for Tennessee to through the ball a lot. Dyson will
catch a fair amount of these passes but don't expect him to score. 

Daunte Culpepper, QB MIN - DRock's Beaatchs Updated 10/12/01
Culpepper could have his best game of the season on Sunday against Detroit.
He's far too valuable to ever place on reserve, so start him with
confidence this week. 

Chris Sanders, WR TEN - Uran Man Updated 10/12/01
Sanders will start Sunday's game if injured receiver Derrick Mason is
unable to play, but don't expect him to be too productive. He lacks the
separation speed to distance himself from the secondary and QB Steve McNair
has had trouble throwing the ball downfield this season.

Cris Carter, WR MIN - Luccis Losers Updated 10/12/01
Carter has struggled, but he's too good not to start on a weekly basis.
Look for him to find the end zone against Detroit on Sunday. 

Byron Chamberlain, TE MIN - Really Rottens Updated 10/12/01
Chamberlain has quickly become one of the key weapons in the Vikings'
passing game, and he is a reliable weekly Fantasy starter. Expect another
good outing this weekend against Detroit. 

Randy Moss, WR MIN - Team Chick Updated 10/12/01
Moss has underachieved thus far, but he'll put up a huge game against
Detroit. The Lions can't seem to stop anyone on defense, so Moss should
have a big day. 

Eddie George, RB TEN - Team Dick Updated 10/12/01
George remains questionable for Sunday's game against Tampa Bay because of
a sprained ankle and will likely be a gametime decision. He missed practice
once again on Thursday. Head coach Jeff Fisher said earlier this week that
George would be a gametime decision if he didn't practice on Thursday or
Friday. He is expected to get a lesser amount of carries even if he does
play. Skip Hicks and Mike Green will get more attempts to lessen George's
load. 

Ricky Williams, RB NO - Uran Man Updated 10/12/01
Williams put up a huge performance against Minnesota last Sunday despite a
shoulder injury. He's a must-start against Carolina, especially after his
solid performance last week. 

Joe Horn, WR NO - President Taft Updated 10/12/01
Horn is a must-start this weekend against Carolina. The Panthers' secondary
is very vulnerable, and Horn has put up good numbers against them in the
past. 

Derrick Mason, WR TEN - C-Dawg's Boyz Updated 10/12/01
Mason missed practice once again on Thursday because of ankle and shoulder
injuries. He remains questionable for Sunday's game. Kevin Dyson and Chris
Sanders will be the starting receivers if Mason is inactive. 

Laveranues Coles, WR NYJ - Team Dick Updated 10/12/01
Coles (knee) is listed as questionable for Sunday's game against the Jets.
Matthew Hatchette would likely start if Coles cannot play.

Cameron Cleeland, TE NO - Free Agent Updated 10/12/01
Cleeland is listed as questionable for Sunday's game against Carolina with
a hamstring injury. He is expected to play, however, but Fantasy owners may
want to consider benching him. He hasn't done much from a Fantasy
perspective, and doesn't seem to be as involved in New Orleans' offense
this season. 

Michael Westbrook, WR WAS - C-Dawg's Boyz Updated 10/12/01
Westbrook (hip) is listed as probable for Monday's game against Dallas. He
could finally have a decent game against the Cowboys, but we don't advise
starting him outside of larger leagues. 

Stephen Alexander, TE WAS - Free Agent Updated 10/12/01
Alexander continues to be a disappointment to Fantasy owners. He's only
good for one or two receptions per game, and his yardage totals are always
minimal. He's not worth starting this week Dallas, and may be better off
left on the waiver wire. 

Rod Gardner, WR WAS - Houston Big Ballers Updated 10/12/01
Gardner could have a decent game against a questionable Dallas secondary on
Monday. He's worth considering as a starter Fantasy-wise, but only in
larger leagues. 

Torry Holt, WR STL - President Taft Updated 10/12/01
Holt has the potential to post big numbers against a shaky N.Y. Giants
secondary on Sunday. He's a big time Fantasy wideout and should be in your
starting lineup on a weekly basis. 

Todd Heap, TE BAL - Free Agent Updated 10/12/01
Heap remains questionable for Sunday's game because of an ankle injury.
Don't bother adding him to your active roster this week. 

Isaac Bruce, WR STL - Uran Man Updated 10/12/01
Bruce hasn't been very consistent thus far, but he's far too talented to
ever consider benching. Look for him to turn things around against CB Jason
Sehorn and the questionable N.Y. Giants secondary. 

Marshall Faulk, RB STL - Blue Balls Updated 10/12/01
Faulk will have another big game this weekend, despite facing a tough N.Y.
Giants defense. He's the top Fantasy player in the league and a must-start
every week. 

Ernie Conwell, TE STL - Free Agent Updated 10/12/01
Conwell (concussion) is probable for Sunday's game against the New York
Giants. He's been a reliable option for Fantasy owners and is worth
starting against the G-Men. 

Kurt Warner, QB STL - Luccis Losers Updated 10/12/01
Considering the huge numbers he puts up on a consistent basis, Warner is a
a must-start every week. He'll post another big game against the New York
Giants on Sunday, so be sure to put him your lineup. 

Nick Goings, RB CAR - Texas Terminators Updated 10/12/01
Goings seems to have slipped to No. 3 on the running back depth chart in
Carolina. He won't see much playing time against New Orleans, so don't
bother using him. 

Chris Weinke, QB CAR - Houston Big Ballers Updated 10/12/01
Weinke may find life tough against a solid New Orleans defense on Sunday.
He's worth considering in larger leagues, but we wouldn't advise starting
him if at all possible. 

Donald Hayes, WR CAR - Luccis Losers Updated 10/12/01
Hayes is listed as probable for Sunday's game against New Orleans due to an
ankle injury. He'll likely be in the starting lineup, however, but it'll be
tough to post solid numbers against the Saints. He's worth considering in
larger leagues only. 

Wesley Walls, TE CAR - Team Chick Updated 10/12/01
Walls is proving that he is still one of the best tight ends in the league
Fantasy-wise. Unless you have a better option, Walls is a must-start
against New Orleans. 

Muhsin Muhammad, WR CAR - Orange Roughy Updated 10/12/01
Muhammad faces a tough New Orleans secondary this weekend, but he's still
too good to consider benching outside of smaller leagues. He is also one of
the more consistent receivers in the league, and should be in your starting
lineup on a weekly basis. 

Patrick Jeffers, WR CAR - C-Dawg's Boyz Updated 10/12/01
Jeffers (knee) could see some action in Sunday's game against New Orleans.
However, he isn't worth starting Fantasy-wise. 

Richard Huntley, RB CAR - Orange Roughy Updated 10/12/01
Huntley will backup Tshimanga Biakabutuka in this weekend's game against
New Orleans. He'll split carries at best, and isn't worth starting
Fantasy-wise. 

Tim Biakabutuka, RB CAR - C-Dawg's Boyz Updated 10/12/01
Biakabutuka is expected to get the start this weekend against New Orleans.
However, we'd advise reserving him if your roster allows you to play a back
with a better matchup. 

Dorsey Levens, RB GB - President Taft Updated 10/12/01
Levens (back) is probable for Sunday's game against Baltimore. He's got no
real value as a Fantasy player at this point. 

Ahman Green, RB GB - Orange Roughy Updated 10/12/01
Green has been one of the best backs in the league thus far, but he could
struggle against Baltimore's vaulted defense. If you have a deep group of
running backs, you may want to consider reserving the Packers' tailback. 

Brett Favre, QB GB - Dont Mess Updated 10/12/01
You might want to consider benching Favre against the ferocious Baltimore
defense this week. He's been great thus far, but if there's ever a game
where he might struggle, it's this contest against the Ravens. 

Bill Schroeder, WR GB - Grid Iron Goons Updated 10/12/01
Schroeder has been great for Fantasy owners thus far, but he'll take a step
back against Baltimore. If you can afford to reserve him, it might be a
good idea to do exactly that. 

Herman Moore, WR DET - C-Dawg's Boyz Updated 10/12/01
Moore has done nothing so far, and we don't expect him to be a reliable
Fantasy player this season. Unless you're desperate, we'd recommend
benching or releasing him. 

James Stewart, RB DET - Orange Roughy Updated 10/12/01
Stewart may not post huge rushing numbers against Minnesota, but he's still
worth starting Fantasy-wise. His numbers are being hampered by Detroit's
struggling offense, but it's tough to bench him considering the lack of
quality backs in the league. 

Germane Crowell, WR DET - Team Dick Updated 10/12/01
Crowell had a decent outing against St. Louis, but he's still not reliable
enough to consider as an everyday starter. Unless you play in deeper
league, we'd advise benching Crowell this week. 

Johnnie Morton, WR DET - Dont Mess Updated 10/12/01
Morton has developed into the Lions' No. 1 receiver this season, and is
worth taking a chance on against Minnesota's mediocre secondary. If you pay
in a deeper league and don't have more reliable options, Morton is
definittly worth considering this week. 

Kerry Collins, QB NYG - Texas Terminators Updated 10/12/01
Collins has struggled the past few weeks, but he has the chance to be very
productive against St. Louis this weekend. The Giants could fall behind
early, so Collins might be asked to throw the ball 30-plus times in the
game. He's worth starting if you don't have a more reliable option. 

Ike Hilliard, WR NYG - Luccis Losers Updated 10/12/01
Hilliard will be the Giants' No. 3 receiving option this weekend against
St. Louis. He's still coming back from foot surgery and probably won't get
enough playing time to warrant a starting spot on your Fantasy team at this
point.

Subject: RE: Hi!
Body:
No, that is the email address I have.  That's what I mean I have been unable to reach him.  Here are his phone numbers from his card but I don't know if they work either.
 
Tim Harbert
(303) 753-8699
(303) 898-9470 Cell
 
Good Luck
Paul

-----Original Message-----
From: Deborah Herbertson [mailto:felinewoman@msn.com]
Sent: Tuesday, October 23, 2001 7:37 PM
To: Lucci, Paul T.
Subject: Re: Hi!


Tried this address.....for Tim......is this a joke???? Just wondering????
Debbe.
 
 

----- Original Message -----
From: Lucci, Paul T.
Sent: Monday, October 22, 2001 4:11 PM
To: Deborah Herbertson
Subject: RE: Hi!
 
Saturday doesn't work for me.  Email Tim at www.discovery@cmconline.com <http://www.discovery@cmconline.com/>.  I think I'm free Thursday night but I may be taking a customer to dinner.  What does Friday night look like?
 

-----Original Message-----
From: Deborah Herbertson [mailto:felinewoman@msn.com]
Sent: Monday, October 22, 2001 3:42 PM
To: Lucci, Paul T.
Subject: Re: Hi!


I have been in a new position (orientation) for the past 4 weeks, and been VERY busy myself.  How about Thursday or Saturday. The only days Carolyn can't would be Wed.'s  
 I think we should all meet somewhere for drinks and go from there. Please e-mail Tim, and also give me his address for Carolyn.
Let me know what you think so I can at least alert Carolyn as well.
Debbe.

----- Original Message -----
From: Lucci, Paul T.
Sent: Monday, October 22, 2001 8:21 AM
To: Deborah Herbertson
Subject: RE: Hi!
 
Hey what are you guys doing partying without me.  Yes I have been traveling, in fact I have been gone almost all October, up through the 15th.  But I'm finished.   When are you thinking of getting together?  

-----Original Message-----
From: Deborah Herbertson [mailto:felinewoman@msn.com]
Sent: Saturday, October 20, 2001 5:41 PM
To: plucci@enron.com
Subject: Hi!


Hi Paul,
 
Ran into "Tim" at Sambuca's Friday night, and he was wondering what happened to our "get together" we were supposed to have several weeks ago????
I told him I hadn't heard back from you, therefore assumed you were not interested. He said he thought you were out of town a great deal, but was going to e-mail you because he wants possibly to set something up with us four. (Myself, Carolyn and you two)
No problem if you are too busy, believe me I understand.........or whatever the reason might be. 
 
Take care,
Debbe.

Franks has caught TD passes in five of six games this year and has become a major scoring threat even though he is not very effective outside of the red zone. Derrick Alexander, WR KC - C-Dawg's Boyz Updated 10/21/01 Alexander finally had a big game, posting 99 yards receiving and a touchdown against Arizona. He's been unreliable for the most part, however, but his potential to post numbers this good makes it tough to bench him. Trent Green, QB KC - Blue Balls Updated 10/21/01 Green threw for 352 yards and a score in Sunday's 24-16 loss to Arizona. Green has been inconsistent this season, however, and no longer warrants a starting nod every week. Doug Chapman, RB MIN - Team Dick Updated 10/21/01 Chapman rushed for 90 yards on 22 carries against the Packers. His numbers were not great, but he was more effective than Michael Bennett has been so far. Chapman may continue to see a good amount of carries if Bennett cannot stay healthy or continues to struggle. David Boston, WR ARI - Blue Balls Updated 10/21/01 Boston had a big game against Kansas City, posting seven receptions for 131 yards and a score. He's emerging as one of the best receivers in the league and is worth starting on a weekly basis. Michael Pittman, RB ARI - Dont Mess Updated 10/21/01 Pittman had a great outing on Sunday against Kansas City, posting 137 yards of total offense and a touchdown. Pittman won't post numbers this good with any regularity, but he's still a valuable player to have on your roster. Jeff Graham, WR SD - Really Rottens Updated 10/21/01 Graham came up huge for San Diego on Sunday, catching seven passes for 107 yards and two scores against Denver. He's still not reliable enough to start on a regular basis, but he's certainly worth a roster spot. LaDainian Tomlinson, RB SD - DRock's Beaatchs Updated 10/21/01 Tomlinson was held in check for the first time this season by Denver on Sunday. The rookie tailback rushed for only 58 yards on the day, but he's still one of the top Fantasy players in the league. Desmond Clark, TE DEN - Free Agent Updated 10/21/01 Clark had a big game on Sunday, catching six passes for 54 yards and a score against San Diego. He's been reliable as far as tight ends go from a Fantasy perspective, so continue to start him on a weekly basis. Brian Griese, QB DEN - Really Rottens Updated 10/21/01 Griese (shoulder) started Sunday's game against San Diego, but he was ineffective. He posted 212 yards passing, a touchdown and two interceptions in Denver's 27-10 loss. Peter Warrick, WR CIN - Dont Mess Updated 10/21/01 Warrick caught eight passes for 84 yards against Chicago. But the potentially explosive wideout is hurting his owners, because he does not find the end zone often. Corey Dillon, RB CIN - Texas Terminators Updated 10/21/01 The Bears held Dillon to just 30 yards on 16 carries. Expect the veteran runner to bounce back from such a quiet performance very quickly. David Terrell, WR CHI - Free Agent Updated 10/21/01 Terrell caught seven passes for 91 yards against Cincinnati. With Marcus Robinson injured, Terrell should assume a more prominent role in the Chicago passing game. Anthony Thomas, RB CHI - President Taft Updated 10/21/01 Thomas rushed for 188 yards and a TD against Cincinnati, clearly establishing himself as Chicago's top RB. Expect him to be the Bears' featured back for the rest of the year. Frank Wycheck, TE TEN - DRock's Beaatchs Updated 10/21/01 Wycheck caught seven passes for 100 yards and a TD at Detroit. Despite some quiet outings until this week, he remains a top-notch Fantasy TE, especially with the Titans lacking in talent at wide receiver. Charlie Batch, QB DET - Free Agent Updated 10/21/01 Batch threw for 338 yards, three TDs and was intercepted once in a loss to Tennessee. Batch has stacked up good numbers in two consecutive weeks, but he remains a Fantasy risk because of his history of inconsistency. Steve McNair, QB TEN - Luccis Losers Updated 10/21/01 McNair threw for 216 yards, a TD and was intercepted twice at Detroit. He completed only 15 of 35 attempts, and many of his throws were inaccurate, possibly indicating he still might be bothered by shoulder problems. Eddie George, RB TEN - Team Dick Updated 10/21/01 George was held to 51 yards on 26 carries by Detroit. The lack of a reliable passing game in Tennessee has certainly hindered his production this year. Shawn Jefferson, WR ATL - Free Agent Updated 10/21/01 Jefferson caught three passes for 67 yards and a TD against the Saints. The speedy wideout has a long history of inconsistency, so don't expect good numbers from him every week. Alge Crumpler, TE ATL - Free Agent Updated 10/21/01 Crumpler caught five passes for 78 yards and a TD against New Orleans. Expect good totals from the big, quick tight end for the remainder of the year. Albert Connell, WR NO - Uran Man Updated 10/21/01 Connell caught only one pass for five yards against Atlanta. It is definitely time to give up on the disappointing wideout. Willie Jackson, WR NO - Texas Terminators Updated 10/21/01 Jackson finished with only 46 receiving yards on five catches against the Falcons. Mediocre numbers against the low-quality Atlanta defense indicate Jackson is not capable of providing owners with regularly good numbers. Hines Ward, WR PIT - Team Chick Updated 10/21/01 Ward was limited to 44 yards on three catches by Tampa Bay. Ward is still making important receptions for the Steelers, but his Fantasy appeal is limited because of Pittsburgh's inability to consistently score in the air. Warrick Dunn, RB TB - President Taft Updated 10/21/01 Dunn played despite a foot injury that had bothered him during the week, but he was limited to 31 yards on 13 carries by a physical Pittsburgh defense. Anthony Becht, TE NYJ - Free Agent Updated 10/21/01 Becht had a huge game against St. Louis, posting five catches for 35 yards and two scores. He's been inconsistent this season, however, but his potential to post good numbers makes him worth starting at a position lacking quality players. Keyshawn Johnson, WR TB - Orange Roughy Updated 10/21/01 Johnson caught 10 passes for 159 yards against Pittsburgh. He has developed a good on-field relationship with QB Brad Johnson. The veteran wideout should continue to post high-quality numbers on a regular basis. Jerome Bettis, RB PIT - Blue Balls Updated 10/21/01 Bettis rushed for 143 yards and a TD on 17 carries against Tampa Bay. He also threw a 32-yard TD pass. His fine outing proves Bettis can compile good numbers against any defense. Trung Canidate, RB STL - Blue Balls Updated 10/21/01 Canidate had a huge game against the New York Jets, posting 232 yards of total offense and two scores. His role as the Rams' featured back may be short-lived, however, depending on the health of stud back Marshall Faulk. Rod Gardner, WR WAS - Houston Big Ballers Updated 10/21/01 Gardner had a huge game on Sunday, posting six catches for 208 yards and a score against Carolina. He seems to have overtaken Michael Westbrook as the No. 1 receiving target in Washington, and is worth a roster spot from a Fantasy perspective. Tony Banks, QB WAS - Free Agent Updated 10/21/01 Banks finally had a somewhat productive game on Sunday, throwing for 346 yards and a score against Carolina. His performance doesn't make him any more valuable from a Fantasy perspective, however, so don't consider him any better than a reserve. Muhsin Muhammad, WR CAR - Orange Roughy Updated 10/21/01 Muhammad was somewhat limited during Sunday's game against Washington due to a nagging rib injury. He caught only two passes for 27 yards in the contest, and may have cost some Fantasy owners a victory this week. James Jackson, RB CLE - Uran Man Updated 10/21/01 Jackson had a surprisingly productive game against Baltimore, rushing for 77 yards and a score. The rookie seems to be all the way back from a nagging rib injury, and is slowly becoming a good Fantasy player. Germane Crowell, WR DET - Team Dick Updated 10/21/01 Crowell was carted off the field in the fourth quarter of Sunday's game with a knee injury. According to published reports, he is likely out for the season. Larry Foster will probably become Detroit's No. 2 receiver for the remainder of the year. Marvin Harrison, WR IND - C-Dawg's Boyz Updated 10/21/01 Harrison had a huge game against New England, posting eight catches for 157 yards and a score. It wasn't enough to win, however, as the Patriots blew out the Colts, 38-17. Colts, DT IND - Orange Roughy Updated 10/21/01 The Colts defense continues to be horrendous, surrending 38 points to Tom Brady and the New England Patriots on Sunday. At this point, the only Fantasy value this unit offers is if you have offensive players facing them in the coming weeks. Troy Brown, WR NE - Houston Big Ballers Updated 10/21/01 Brown had a huge game against Indianapolis, catching eight passes for 120 yards and a score. He continues to establish himself as a reliable Fantasy player, and may even better once Terry Glenn returns from a hamstring injury. Eddie Kennison, WR DEN - Dont Mess Updated 10/21/01 Kennison suffered an apparent head/neck injury during the first quarter of Sunday's game against San Diego. He left the contest but later returned to action. David Patten, WR NE - Grid Iron Goons Updated 10/21/01 Patten had a record-setting game against Indianapolis on Sunday. The wideout had four total touchdowns (two receiving, one passing and one rushing) as the Patriots took out the Colts, 38-17. Patten will likely be moved to third on the depth chart once Terry Glenn returns, but he's certainly worth a roster spot at this point. Tony Banks, QB WAS - Free Agent Updated 10/21/01 Banks left Sunday's game against Carolina in the fourth quarter due to a hand injury. Kent Graham replaced Banks for a play, but he did return. Tim Biakabutuka, RB CAR - C-Dawg's Boyz Updated 10/21/01 Biakabutuka left Sunday's game against Washington in the fourth quarter after sustaining a foot injury. He didn't return to the game, and X-rays later revealed a break. He did put up 150 yards of total offense and a touchdown before sustaining the injury, but that may have been his last game of the season. Bill Schroeder, WR GB - Grid Iron Goons Updated 10/21/01 Schroeder will be inactive for Sunday's game at Minnesota. Corey Bradford is expected to start in his place. Vinny Testaverde, QB NYJ - Uran Man Updated 10/21/01 Testaverde was replaced by Chad Pennington in the second half of Sunday's game against St. Louis. The move wasn't injury related, but simply Jets' coach Herm Edwards giving Pennington some playing time in a blowout game. Testaverde finished the afternoon 9-of-13 for 74 yards with a touchdown and an interception. Elvis Grbac, QB BAL - Houston Big Ballers Updated 10/21/01 Grbac suffered a chest injury during the second half of Sunday's game against Cleveland. Randall Cunningham took over for Grbac, who did not return to the game. Grbac's status for next weekend's game against Jacksonville is uncertain. Terry Allen, RB BAL - Texas Terminators Updated 10/21/01 Allen left Sunday's game against Cleveland with a calf injury. Jason Brookins received most of the carries in Allen's absence. Dennis Northcutt, WR CLE - Free Agent Updated 10/21/01 Northcutt left Sunday's game against Baltimore with an undisclosed injury. He was replaced by rookie Quincy Morgan. Wayne Chrebet, WR NYJ - Dont Mess Updated 10/21/01 Chrebet suffered his second concussion in as many weeks during Sunday's game against St. Louis. The Jets' wideout did not return to the game and will be re-evaluated on Monday. Marcus Robinson, WR CHI - President Taft Updated 10/21/01 Robinson suffered an apparently serious knee injury in the second quarter of Sunday's game. He was carted off the field and will not return. The initial diagnosis was a sprain, although the injury appeared to be more serious. Michael Bennett, RB MIN - Houston Big Ballers Updated 10/21/01 Bennett has now been listed as inactive for Sunday's game against Green Bay. Doug Chapman will start at tailback for the Vikings in his absence. Patrick Jeffers, WR CAR - C-Dawg's Boyz Updated 10/21/01 Jeffers (knees) has been ruled out of the game against Washington. He has been practicing recently, and could return to action in the near future, though. Tony Richardson, RB KC - Team Chick Updated 10/21/01 Richardson (shoulder) will not play this week against the Cardinals. Priest Holmes will continue to see a full workload as the Chiefs' featured back. Torrance Small, WR NE - Free Agent Updated 10/21/01 According to published reports, Small has been released by the New England Patriots. It is the second time this season that the team has cut Small, who was likely let go due to Terry Glenn's return from a suspension. Fred Taylor, RB JAC - Dont Mess Updated 10/21/01 According to the Florida Times-Union, Taylor will miss the Jags' Oct. 28 contest against Baltimore. Head Coach Tom Coughlin would not offer up a timetable for Taylor's return, so Fantasy owners must continue to play the waiting game. Doug Chapman, RB MIN - Team Dick Updated 10/21/01 Chapman has officially been named the Vikings' starting tailback for Sunday's game against Green Bay. He may lose carries in the red zone to Travis Prentice, but Chapman is still worth starting if you're desperate for a running back this week. Quincy Morgan, WR CLE - Uran Man Updated 10/21/01 Morgan will drop down to the No. 3 receiver on the depth chart this weekend against Baltimore. Dennis Northcutt is finally healthy and will make the start, but neither receiver is worth starting from a Fantasy perspective. Dennis Northcutt, WR CLE - Free Agent Updated 10/21/01 According to published reports, Northcutt will start ahead of rookie Quincy Morgan on Sunday. Cleveland will be facing a fired up Ravens' defense, however, so starting any Browns' wideout this week is risky. Wayne Chrebet, WR NYJ - Dont Mess Updated 10/21/01 Chrebet (concussion) completed his first full practice of the week on Friday, according to the St. Louis Post-Dispatch. He's expected to start against the Rams on Sunday, but he may have trouble facing CB Aeneas Willliams, so we'd recommend reserving him if possible. Warrick Dunn, RB TB - President Taft Updated 10/21/01 According to the Tampa Tribune, Dunn has missed some practice time this week due to his sprained foot. He is expected to start on Sunday against Pittsburgh, however, so Fantasy owners should have no hesitation in starting him this week. Corey Bradford, WR GB - Free Agent Updated 10/21/01 Bradford is expected to start in place of the injured Bill Schroeder on Sunday against Minnesota. He's worth taking a chance on in deeper leagues, but don't expect him to post Schroeder-like numbers. Bill Schroeder, WR GB - Grid Iron Goons Updated 10/21/01 Schroeder (ankle) has been downgraded to questionable for Sunday's game against Minnesota. He'll almost certainly be replaced by Corey Bradford in the starting lineup, so starting him from a Fantasy perspective is a risky move. Terrence Wilkins, WR IND - Free Agent Updated 10/21/01 Wilkins (ribs) is out for Sunday's game against New England, and may be lost until November 4. With Jerome Pathon ailing as well, rookie Reggie Wayne will be the No. 2 receiver for the Colts. Jermaine Lewis, WR BAL - Free Agent Updated 10/21/01 According to the Baltimore Sun, Lewis (hamstring) has not been 100 percent healthy this season. He's expected to play on Sunday against Cleveland, however, but he's not worth starting outside of deeper Fantasy leagues. Todd Heap, TE BAL - Free Agent Updated 10/21/01 Heap (ankle) practiced on Friday and is expected to play on Sunday against Cleveland. He's worth starting in deeper leagues, but the presence of Shannon Sharpe will keep him from being productive on a consistent basis. Derrick Mason, WR TEN - C-Dawg's Boyz Updated 10/21/01 Mason (ankle) is expected to start on Sunday against Detroit. With the Lions' secondary in shambles, starting Mason is a good decision for Fantasy owners with a thin group of receivers. Erron Kinney, TE TEN - Free Agent Updated 10/21/01 Kinney is dealing with a slight calf strain, but he's expected to play on Sunday against Detroit. With Frank Wycheck in the picture, it's tough to depend on Kinney to produce consistently, so benching him is advisable. Rob Moore, WR ARI - Free Agent Updated 10/21/01 Moore (hamstring) missed practice on Friday and has been downgraded to out for Sunday's game against New Orleans. Keep him on reserve if he's currently on your roster Brian Griese, QB DEN - Really Rottens Updated 10/21/01 Griese (shoulder) will start Sunday's game against the San Diego Chargers. He has practiced with the first team offense all week, and seemed to have no problems mechanically. These AFC West games tend to be high scoring, so starting Griese is advisable. Lions, DT DET - Free Agent Updated 10/21/01 Defensive back Bryant Westbrook has been listed as out for Sunday's game against Tennessee. This could mean big things for Steve McNair and the Titans' passing game, who should have an easy time beating Detroit's corners on a regular basis. Terry Glenn, WR NE - Grid Iron Goons Updated 10/21/01 According to published reports, Glenn has been declared inactive for Sunday's game against Indianapolis. Glenn is dealing with a hamstring injury that he sustained last week, and he is not yet 100 percent. Marshall Faulk, RB STL - Blue Balls Updated 10/21/01 According to the St. Louis Post-Dispatch, Faulk has been ruled out for Sunday's game against the New York Jets. Faulk missed his third straight practice on Friday, so the team will go with Trung Canidate as the featured back. Mike Alstott, RB TB - Luccis Losers Updated 10/19/01 Don't expect much from Alstott this week. Warrick Dunn is healthy enough to start again, and will be the featured back against Pittsburgh. Johnnie Morton, WR DET - Dont Mess Updated 10/19/01 Morton could have a big game this weekend against Tennessee. The Titans' secondary has been shaky at best, so the positive matchup makes Morton a good start from a Fantasy perspective. James Stewart, RB DET - Orange Roughy Updated 10/19/01 Stewart will have a hard time racking up good Fantasy stats Sunday against a Tennessee linebacking corps that can cover a lot of ground. Start him only if you don't have two other backs on your team with better matchups. Byron Chamberlain, TE MIN - Really Rottens Updated 10/19/01 Chamberlain is definitely a good start this week. He will become a major factor if the Packers focus too much on Minnesota's wide receivers. Marty Booker, WR CHI - Luccis Losers Updated 10/19/01 Booker would make an excellent Fantasy starter in his game Sunday against the Bengals. Cincinnati is without cornerback Rodney Heath, which will make it difficult to defend Booker this week. Cris Carter, WR MIN - Luccis Losers Updated 10/19/01 Expect good numbers from Carter this week. He is a big-game player who will not be flustered by the improved Green Bay defense. Marcus Robinson, WR CHI - President Taft Updated 10/19/01 Robinson battled a back injury in Week Five, but he should rebound on Sunday against Cincinnati. The Bears will need to make some deep passes and we think Robinson would make a solid Fantasy starter this week. Daunte Culpepper, QB MIN - DRock's Beaatchs Updated 10/19/01 Green Bay's defense has played well so far, but Culpepper won't be intimidated by the Packers. He has faced them many times before, and should fare well in an important divisional game in front of the home crowd. Jim Miller, QB CHI - Grid Iron Goons Updated 10/19/01 Miller will need to throw the deep ball often Sunday against the overaggressive Bengals. He should post adequate Fantasy numbers, making him a solid starter if you don't have any other superstar QBs to choose from. Ahman Green, RB GB - Orange Roughy Updated 10/19/01 Green will get the bulk of his numbers in the second half if Green Bay can get ahead of Minnesota early. He will definitely be good for at least one TD. Brett Favre, QB GB - Dont Mess Updated 10/19/01 Favre should have another excellent game this week. Minnesota's secondary will not be able to handle him, especially with CB Robert Tate ailing. Warrick Dunn, RB TB - President Taft Updated 10/19/01 Dunn sat out practice Thursday with a sprained right big toe, but is expected to play Sunday against Pittsburgh. He faces a tough challenge in the Steelers' stingy rush defense, so consider reserving him if you have a more established back on your roster. Bill Schroeder, WR GB - Grid Iron Goons Updated 10/19/01 Schroeder missed practice for a second straight day Thursday due to an ankle injury. However, he is listed as probable on the injury report, and you should probably start him this week unless he takes a turn for the worse before gametime. Randy Moss, WR MIN - Team Chick Updated 10/19/01 Moss practiced Thursday for the first time since aggravating an ankle injury on Sunday, and has been upgraded from questionable to probable on the injury report for Sunday's game against Green Bay. You should definitely get him into your active Fantasy lineup as a result. Shane Matthews, QB CHI - Free Agent Updated 10/19/01 Matthews could serve as the backup quarterback for the Bears Sunday in Cincinnati after throwing in drills Thursday. Don't bother with him, as he's not going to get much playing time the rest of the season behind Jim Miller on the depth chart. Fred Baxter, TE CHI - Free Agent Updated 10/19/01 Baxter practiced Thursday and hopes to be able to play Sunday in Cincinnati, according to the Chicago Sun-Times. He has been recovering from a neck injury, but isn't worth your Fantasy attention. Brian Griese, QB DEN - Really Rottens Updated 10/19/01 Griese (shoulder) practiced with the first-team offense, and looked good, Mike Shanahan told the Denver Post. He is expected to start against San Diego. "I think he did pretty good," coach Mike Shanahan said. "He practiced the whole practice. It didn't look like there was anything wrong. I'm not sure how painful it is because I haven't talked to him, but so far, so good." Terrence Wilkins, WR IND - Free Agent Updated 10/19/01 Wilkins (ribs) is not expected to play against the Patriots. He is listed as doubtful. Wayne Chrebet, WR NYJ - Dont Mess Updated 10/19/01 The effects of a concussion suffered against Miami has kept Chrebet out of practices this week. He is expected to play against St. Louis. J.R. Redmond, RB NE - Team Dick Updated 10/19/01 Redmond (ankle) is expected to be in uniform for Sunday's game. But it appears he will not be used much, because New England has found Antowain Smith to be a dependable back. Desmond Clark, TE DEN - Free Agent Updated 10/19/01 Clark should get open often against San Diego. The Chargers' pass defense can definitely be exploited over the middle. Rod Smith, WR DEN - Blue Balls Updated 10/19/01 Smith should have another fine game this week. He will be the focal point of the Denver passing game in a contest that will feature a lot of offense. Mike Anderson, RB DEN - Really Rottens Updated 10/19/01 Anderson may find it difficult to reach 100 yards against the Chargers. San Diego has a strong front seven, and the Broncos are having trouble with blocking on end runs. Freddie Jones, TE SD - DRock's Beaatchs Updated 10/19/01 Jones has been a disappointment so far, but he could be a factor this week, as the Chargers trade blows with the Broncos in a high-scoring game. Jeff Graham, WR SD - Really Rottens Updated 10/19/01 Graham should produce good numbers this week. The Chargers will probably engage in a high-scoring game with the Broncos. Tony Gonzalez, TE KC - Grid Iron Goons Updated 10/19/01 Gonzalez will be a prime target against the Cardinals. Kansas City will certainly see many passing openings over the middle. Chris Thomas, WR KC - Uran Man Updated 10/19/01 Thomas has moved into Kansas City's starting lineup. Don't use him unless you are desperate for help at receiver. Derrick Alexander, WR KC - C-Dawg's Boyz Updated 10/19/01 The matchup suggests Alexander will do well this week, but the Chiefs will probably look to keep the ball on the ground, limiting Kansas City's passing numbers. Frank Wycheck, TE TEN - DRock's Beaatchs Updated 10/19/01 Don't expect Wycheck to catch a lot of passes this weekend. He hasn't been featured too heavily in the Titans' passing game and has been used more to block for running back Eddie George. Derrick Mason, WR TEN - C-Dawg's Boyz Updated 10/19/01 Mason is suffering from an ankle injury and is listed as questionable for this week's game against the Lions. Tennessee expects him to play but don't rely on him being too productive. The injury caused him to miss last week's game. +--------------------------------------------------------------------------+ | Transactions, View 3 Days, All But Lineup, All Teams | +--------------------------------------------------------------------------+ Transactions DATE TIME PLAYER TEAM TRANSACTION EFFECTIVE COST 10/19/01 9:04 AM Dyson, Kevin Team Chick Signed Week 6 10/19/01 9:04 AM Mayes, Derrick Team Chick Released Week 6 10/19/01 9:04 AM Carswell, Dwayne Team Chick Signed Week 6 10/19/01 9:04 AM Dudley, Rickey Team Chick Released Week 6 +--------------------------------------------------------------------------+ | Schedule, Breakdown Current, Luccis Losers | +--------------------------------------------------------------------------+ DRock's Beaatchs at Luccis Losers PLAYER POS POINTS PLAYER POS POINTS Culpepper, Daunte QB 29.0 Warner, Kurt QB 10.0 Mack, Stacey RB 8.0 Staley, Duce RB 0.0 Tomlinson, LaDainian RB 6.0 Booker, Marty WR 12.0 Freeman, Antonio WR 5.0 Carter, Cris WR 12.0 Price, Peerless WR 0.0 Hakim, Az-Zahir WR 10.0 Taylor, Travis WR 0.0 Cleeland, Cameron TE 7.0 Vinatieri, Adam K 10.0 Akers, David K 0.0 Buccaneers DT 5.0 Ravens DT 2.0 TOTAL 63.0 TOTAL 53.0 +--------------------------------------------------------------------------+ | Copyright 2001 Commissioner.COM Inc and SportsLine.com Inc. | | Your site is always at http://football.fantasy.sportsline.com/getbad | +--------------------------------------------------------------------------+ FB10SP -- EnronData.org (http://enrondata.org) Reference Enron Datasets

Subject: Match.com Email Undeliverable: Cannot locate you
Body:
We received your email addressed to poblet@talkmatch.com. Unfortunately, we cannot find your username or email address listed as a current member or subscriber of Match.com. 

Membership at Match.com is free and allows you to search the profiles of millions of quality singles, post your own profile, view your best personal matches, receive new matches by email, and more. But to make anonymous contact with profiles that catch your eye, you must join as a paid subscriber. For details, click here: http://www.Match.com/help/faq.asp?#D

If you are a current subscriber and believe you've received this email in error, please contact our Customer Care Team at: customercare@match.com

For your convenience, we've included the text of your personal message below:

To: poblet@talkmatch.com
Subject: RE: Match.com - You've Got Mail: Hello Again!
I would tell people, and in fact have told people.  The way I figure it
is that as long as I try and have fun with it, it will be fun, and if it
gets out of hand I'll quit.  I just started with this also.  I had a
female friend that got involved with something like this and than
totally freaked out when people found out.  So, when I signed up I
called to tell her what I had done.  She thought I was messing with her
and got mad again.  Since then she has realized I was serious and now, I
feel, she has become less serious about the whole deal.
 
Anyway,  the reason I signed up was that it seems like a good idea.  You
can meet new people without sticking your neck out too far.  So what
about you, where do you work and live, what part of town?  What do you
do in your spare time?  Etc?  
 
    

	-----Original Message----- 
	From: Poblet@talkmatch.com 
	Sent: Mon 11/26/2001 9:29 PM 
	To: plucci@enron.com 
	Cc: 
	Subject: Re: Match.com - You've Got Mail: Hello Again!
	
	

	I'm putting one up - I just sent it in to be
	scanned/approved, whatever they do, I just didn't at
	first because I wasn't really gung ho about doing this
	- I sort of just filled out the profile and sat back.
	But I think it's actually pretty cool.  I'm surprised
	there are so many normal people doing this, aren't
	you?  So, what made you decide to do this?  And will
	you ever tell anyone that you did/are???

Subject: RE: Bob Picks Indy
Body:
Pool Update:

Here's where things stand:

The pool will continue.  I'm still waiting to here back from Dave Heinemen,
Nathan Dougherty and Mark Hull to find out what they want to do.  For those
that responded so promptly....Thank you.   I'll be in Houston tomorrow and
out of the office Thursday.  Please send me your pick by 10:00 am Friday.  


Alex Woodruff and Jerry Padilla have elected to collect their money now.
You'll receive your money when Bob resumes his "Pool Director" chair next
week.  

Enjoy your day!
Larry Bevans

OK that whole bra comment...MEAN!  You know I'm sensitive about my little breasts!  I've been working on the girls about the limo.  I think they're coming around.  It would be much less expensive to go the limo way in my opinion.  Plus, I'm not crazy about running around in the cold since I  won't be wearing much!

----- Original Message ----- 
From: Lucci, Paul T. <mailto:Paul.T.Lucci@ENRON.com> 
To: lisab <mailto:lisab@int.iwhm.com> 
Sent: Wednesday, October 24, 2001 10:38 AM
Subject: RE: halloween

What parties are you going to.  I've got two parties and a band I want tos ee.  Cabs are too expensive.  Figure out where you guys want to go and then let's talk.  What are you going as, hopefully cat woman in as kin-tight cat suit.  So you better pad your bra! 

-----Original Message-----

Sent: Wednesday, October 24, 2001 10:31 AM
To: Lucci, Paul T.
Subject: halloween


Update!  Jeff the DUI guy wants to party, so no go on the driving.  Like I guessed, Nat and Lorena are going to pass on the limo.  So, taxi is probably the best bet.  We're meeting at Nat's place in the early evening to "get ready" and then planning to hit the bars and maybe a couple of parties.  Are you going to join us?   Do you know of anything going on?

Body:

You are receiving these e-reports because you have signed up for CBS SportsLine.com Fantasy Football. To customize, reschedule, or turn off these reports please click here

NFL Reports, Player Updates 
Latest NFL Player News

James Stewart, RB DET - Orange Roughy Updated 11/18/01
Stewart (ankle) is out for Sunday's game against Arizona. However, coach Marty Mornhinweg stated that Stewart is making progress, and is getting closer to returning to action.

Marco Battaglia, TE CIN - Free Agent Updated 11/18/01
Battaglia (appendectomy) is out at least a month, and may miss the rest of the season. The big tight end has no real value as a Fantasy player.

Mark Brunell, QB JAC - President Taft Updated 11/18/01
Brunell (quadriceps) will start on Sunday against Pittsburgh. He'll be facing a tough Steelers' secondary at less than 100 percent, however, so Fantasy owners may want to consider benching him in Week 10.

Fred Taylor, RB JAC - Dont Mess Updated 11/18/01
Taylor (groin) practiced without incident on Friday, but he still needs medical clearance before he can play in Sunday's game against Pittsburgh. Even is he is able to play, however, he'd only be used on a limited basis. Stacey Mack will get the start in any event, so playing Taylor on your Fantasy team is not a wise move.

Jerome Pathon, WR IND - Team Dick Updated 11/18/01
Pathon (foot) is out for Sunday's game against New Orleans, according to the Indianapolis Star. Reggie Wayne will start in Pathon's place once again.

James Jackson, RB CLE - Uran Man Updated 11/18/01! Jackson (ankle) will likely be a gametime decison on Sunday against Baltimore. If the rookie tailback is unable to play, Jamel White will be Cleveland's featured back with Benjamin Gay getting some looks in the backfield as well.

Correll Buckhalter, RB PHI - Uran Man Updated 11/17/01
Buckhalter has been suspended for this weekend's game against Dallas. He is one of three Eagles who will be held out of the game. Brian Mitchell will likely serve as Duce Staley's backup.

Jamal Lewis, RB BAL - Free Agent Updated 11/17/01
According to published reports, Lewis has been suspended for four games. Lewis' four-game suspension went into effect on Friday and he will not be allowed to work out or rehabilitate with the team for four weeks, or until Dec. 17. Instead, Lewis will work toward recovering from a torn ACL in Tennessee.

Tyrone Wheatley, RB OAK - Uran Man Updated 11/16/01
Wheatley (knee) is out for Sunday's game with the Chargers. Charlie Garner will once again be Oakland's feature back. Zack Crockett may be used in goal-line situations.

Frank Wycheck, TE TEN - DRock's Beaatchs Updated 11/16/01!
According to published reports, Wycheck is expected to play half of Sunday's game against Cincinnati. That makes him a risky start from a Fantasy perspective.

Steve McNair, QB TEN - Luccis Losers Updated 11/16/01
McNair's status is still in question for Sunday's game against Cincinnati due to an injured right thumb. He threw the ball during individual drills Friday, and according to published reports, is likely to play despite not being 100 percent. We don't recommend McNair this week as a result.

Emmitt Smith, RB DAL - Team Dick Updated ! 11! /16/01
Smith will return to the lineup Sunday against Philadelphia after missing two games with a sprained right knee. Cowboys Head Coach Dave Campo said after Friday's practice that Smith would "be ready to play the majority of the game." His return bumps Troy Hambrick to fullback, but we wouldn't recommend you use either back against the stingy Eagles rush defense.

Frank Sanders, WR ARI - Dont Mess Updated 11/16/01
Sanders (hamstring) was added to the NFL injury report on Friday and is now listed as questionable for Sunday's game against Detroit. However, if you're completely desperate for a wideout in a larger league this week, Sanders' matchup against a vulnerable Detroit secondary is worth considering as long as he! 's! able to play.

Chris Weinke, QB CAR - Houston Big Ballers Updated 11/16/01
According to published reports, Weinke will be the starting quarterback for Sunday's game against San Francisco. However, he's not worth starting on your Fantasy team.

Daunte Culpepper, QB MIN - DRock's Beaatchs Updated 11/16/01
Culpepper is one pace for a good Fantasy season despite the lack of consistency in Minnesota's offense this season. He's one of the better quarterbacks in the league from a Fantasy perspective, and should be in your starting lineup on a weekly basis.

Cris Carter, WR MIN - Luccis Losers Updated 11/16/01
Carter's numbers may be down somewhat this season, but he's still too good to ever consider benching. The veteran has a knack for finding the end zone, and should have a good game against rookie CB Will Allen and the Giants' secondary on Monday night.

Randy Moss, WR MIN - Team Chick Updat! ed! 11/16/01
Moss is listed as probable for Monday's game against the N.Y. Giants due to an ankle injury. He's been underachieving this season, but it's almost impossible to bench him based on his potential to post solid Fantasy numbers.

Ricky Williams, RB NO - Uran Man Updated 11/16/01
Williams is one of the better Fantasy backs in the league, and is a good player to use on a weekly basis. He'll face an Indianapolis defense that has been underachieving all season long, so Williams is a must-start.

Aaron Brooks, QB NO - Grid Iron Goons Updated 11/16/01
Brooks had a big game against San Francisco last weekend, throwing for 347 yards and two scores. He may be a bit inconsistent this season, but his potential to post huge numbers makes it tough to bench him, especially against a vulnerable Indianapolis defense.

Willie Jackson, WR NO - Grid Iron Goons Updated 11/16/01
Jackson put up a huge game against San Francisco last weekend, posting 11 catches and 167 yards receiving. He'll face a questionable Indianapolis squad that is vulnerable to the pass in Week 10, so starting Jackson this week is a solid option.

Stephen Davis, RB WAS - Houston Big Ballers Updated 11/16/01
Davis has stepped up his play after beginning the season slowly. He's averaged 112 yards rushing over his last four games, and is once again emerging as a reliable Fantasy player. Give him the start in Week 10 against a Denver defense that is vulnerable to high scoring games.

Tony Banks, QB WAS - Free Agent Updated 11/16/01
Banks has played well of late, throwing five touchdowns in his last three games. He's got a good matchup this weekend against a Denver team that can be beaten through the air, but he's only worth considering in very deep Fantasy leagues.

Michael Westbrook, WR WAS - C-Dawg's Boyz Updated 11/16/01
Westbrook has been inconsistent this season, but he has caught three touchdown passes in his last four games. He'll face a Denver secondary this weekend that is vulnerable at best, so starting him in deeper leagues is worth considering.

Rod Gardner, WR WAS - Houston Big Ballers Updated 11/16/01
Gardner has been held in check in his last two games, catching only three passes for 38 yards. He does have a favorable matchup this weekend against Denver, however, so starting him is a good move.

Az-Zahir Hakim, WR STL - Luccis Losers Updated 11/16/01
Hakim has been inconsistent in recent weeks, so starting him on your Fantasy team is a gamble unless the matchup is right. He'll go up against a tough New England secondary in Week Ten, so avoid using him outside of deeper leagues.

Torry Holt, WR STL - President Taft Updated 11/16/01
Holt continues to put up consistent yardage totals, but he's only scored only three touchdowns this season. He'll face a tough New England secondary this weekend, but he's still worth starting on your Fantasy team based on his potential to put up solid numbers.

Isaac Bruce, WR STL - Uran Man Updated 11/16/01
Bruce hasn't put up the huge Fantasy totals this season, but he's still one of the better wideouts in the league. He'll face CB Ty Law and the formidable New England secondary, but he's still worth starting based on his potential for big numbers.

Marshall Faulk, RB STL - Blue Balls U! pd! ated 11/16/01
Faulk had a huge game against Carolina, proving that he is still the best Fantasy player in the league. He's a must-start every week, and should post solid numbers in Week 10 against New England.

Ernie Conwell, TE STL - C-Dawg's Boyz Updated 11/16/01
Conwell has had a few down weeks, so starting him on your Fantasy team is somewhat of a gamble. With the lack of depth at tight end around the league, however, starting Conwell is something many Fantasy owners will have no choice but to do.

Richard Huntley, RB CAR - Orange Roughy Updated 11/16/01
Huntley will be the likely starter this weekend against San Francisco, but don't be surprised if he splits carries with Nick Goings. Avoid starting either back in Week 10 if at all possible.
